<subSubSection pageNumber="292" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="292">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="292">Note:</emphasis>
Specific epithet spelled 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“polydactylon”">&quot;polydactylon&quot;</normalizedToken>
in the protologue. The protologue of this name included an explicit reference to the earlier 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="292">Amoen. Acad.</emphasis>
5: 412 (1760) (a reprint of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="292">Pl. Jamaic. Pugillus</emphasis>
) where 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1759)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Andropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barbatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="292">A barbatus</emphasis>
L. (1759)
</taxonomicName>
was the binomial used. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Andropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polydactylos">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="292">Andropogon polydactylos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is therefore illegitimate.
</paragraph>
